text:
Bike Night
What's better than biking in winter? Biking in the winter in fresh snow. And what's better than biking in the winter in fresh snow? Biking in the winter in fresh snow at night. Around 2.7 million people live in Chicago, but on a night like this I can ride for miles along the lakefront in solutide. It's a beautiful thing.
Nice:)
"What's better than biking in winter?" You're kidding, John. A somewhat eerie solemn scene with a circle of light. Along the lake? You're tough!
I like this one. A lot. :)
Awesome shot
Fantastic addition to the series!
Love the scale and perspective. Well done!
Wonderful John with those circles of light surrounding your bike.
Cool, literally. I much prefer warmth but will cheer you on :)
Great shot
... i think, these cycled majestic empty solitude dressed in white fine mood - what a fascinating feeling ... love it ...
Excellent!!!
stopped me in my tracks
Fabulous!! You captured a moment that made me stop ✨
splendide moment bien particulier, très bien capturé

While I can't agree with your progression of "what's better" I love this shot- wonderful circular light pattern on the snow, which has been carefully approached so as not to disturb the foreground.  Beautiful simple shot, well rendered in the warm mono.
i like how the circle of light is echoed in the snow. beautiful solitude. both in the image and in your experience. i love this winter-biking series.
favolosa
This has to be one of the best images I’ve seen. Your creativity knows no bounds. Brilliant my good friend.

I am so loving your winter biking series, John! This has got to be one of the best bike shots I've seen, besides your last one :) Fantastic minimalism - there is such a sense of aloneness and yet excitement and fun. Such a creative and wonderful image!
Beautiful capture
an excellent composition my friend
Love it, such beautiful tones and mood!
And when you do your mind is free to explore, with your heart you will see even in the dark, and maybe more so.

Wow, it is amazing to find that much solitude in a big city!
Your photo illustrates your point beautifully. I love how you either managed to make no footprints or you photoshopped them out... it is perfect. Great idea for your bike series, the night time street light!

I would have never guessed a bicycle could so perfectly compliment the variety of winter landscapes you encounter. The unlikely juxtapositions and your eye for composition command attention and contemplation. Bravo!
So beautiful, so lonely, so elegant.
Wowww
Fantastic minimalism, man !
Looks like a great view John! I like the way you managed the tracks in the snow!  Interesting too in that the thumbnail looks like a big white candle!

Excellent shot ... very nice photo!
Great capture!
